(24, 'Conflict Sensitivity Assessment', 'Humanitarian', 6, '[\"1\"]', '[\"4\"]', '[\"100\"]', 'Completed', 0, 'Assessment', 'The conflict sensitivity assessment will inform the project to design the activities and aims to ensure a contextually appropriate project setup and implementation with a child-centered focus. It also aims to mitigate potential harm and identify context-sensitive outcomes across all sectors, with a specific focus on child-centred considerations.', '1721808493_Screenshot 2024-07-24 130732.png', '1721808493_CSA FINAL REPORT.pdf', 12, 1, '2024-01-26 09:16:25', '2024-07-24 08:08:13'),
(25, 'Post KAP Survey', 'Development', 7, '[\"6\",\"4\"]', '[\"4\",\"2\"]', '[\"38\",\"167\",\"174\",\"179\"]', 'Completed', 0, 'Evaluation', 'Save the Children International (SCI) Pakistan Country Office, with funding from Unilever  Limited implemented the Hygiene & Behaviour Change Coalition 2022 (HBCC-2022) in the four major districts in Pakistan i.e. Karachi, Thatta, Peshawar and Chitral. The project was implemented to increase the knowledge and abilities of children regarding hygiene and improve the water, sanitation, and hygiene (WASH) infrastructure in targeted schools to provide better access to personal hygiene and to promote hygiene practices and COVID-19 vaccination uptake in preventing the future outbreaks in the targeted districts.', '1721808305_Screenshot 2024-07-24 130028.png', '1721808305_Post-KAP Survey Report - HBCC II - Final Draft.pdf', 12, 1, '2024-02-01 10:33:39', '2024-07-24 08:05:06'),
(26, 'Pre KAP Survey', 'Development', 7, '[\"6\",\"4\"]', '[\"4\",\"2\"]', '[\"38\",\"167\",\"174\",\"179\"]', 'Completed', 0, 'Assessment', 'The HBCC-II project aims to expand upon SCI’s previous efforts to promote good hygiene and address COVID-19 vaccine hesitancy through mass media campaigns and the use of social media. These campaigns are to utilize strategies and content that have been developed and tested in HBCC Phase-I and the Adaptive Communication and Technology for Increasing Vaccination Acceptance and Teen Engagement (ACTIVATE) project. The ACTIVATE pilot campaign specifically focused on developing and evaluating tools for effective social behavior change, using evidence-based techniques such as behavior science, A/B testing, social listening, youth engagement, and regional engagement. \r\nIn the second phase of the project i.e., HBCC-II, the focus is to develop campaign content and run a mass media and social media campaigns on better hygiene practices and enhance COVID vaccine uptake to effectively reach target communities in four selected districts namely Peshawar and Chitral in Khyber Pakhtunkhwa and Karachi, and Thatta in Sindh province.', '1721808269_Screenshot 2024-07-24 130337.png', '1721808269_Pre-KAPs Survey Report - HBCC II_Updated Draft_100223_Final.docx', 12, 1, '2024-02-01 10:40:59', '2024-07-24 08:04:29'),
(27, 'Baseline Study', 'Humanitarian', 6, '[\"5\",\"6\",\"3\",\"1\"]', '[\"4\"]', '[\"100\"]', 'Completed', 0, 'Assessment', 'The baseline report presents a comprehensive examination of the current circumstances of communities impacted by the 2022 floods in selected union councils, Sindhi Butra and Burira, within Dadu district, Sindh. The overarching objective is to establish benchmarks crucial for effective project planning, implementation, and the ongoing monitoring of progress. Employing a mix of quantitative and qualitative methodologies, the study emphasizes the utilization of participatory techniques during data collection.\r\n\r\nThe assessment encompassed 356 households, with 281 in Sindhi Butra and 75 in Burira. The gender representation was balanced, with 52% being females and 48% males. Among the heads of households, 32% were aged between 40 to 49 years. The findings revealed multifaceted challenges spanning shelter, water, sanitation, agriculture, livestock, child wellbeing, and social conflicts. A notable 60% of them were found to be illiterate, with an additional 19% having only primary education.', '1721807953_Screenshot 2024-07-24 125844.png', '1721807953_ECHO-ERADA Baseline Report_Clean_Final (240328).pdf', 12, 1, '2024-02-01 10:47:22', '2024-07-24 07:59:13'),
(28, 'Multi Sectoral Rapid Need Assessment', 'Humanitarian', 5, '[\"6\",\"3\",\"4\",\"1\",\"2\"]', '[\"3\"]', '[\"71\",\"74\",\"75\",\"77\"]', 'Completed', 0, 'Assessment', 'Save the Children conducted a Multi-sectoral Rapid Needs Assessment (MSRNA) in January 2024 to assess the needs of the Host and Afghan’s refugee communities in Quetta, Killa Saifullah, Pishin and Loralai Districts of Balochistan. Report is also compiled and made available on January 20, 2024. The purpose of the MSRNA was to explore the immediate needs of people regarding Education, Protection, Health & Nutrition, Food security, and WASH. A mixed method research approach was applied to collect the quantitative and qualitative information from children including girls, boys and adults including women, men of society to explore their needs. A purposeful random sampling method was followed while selecting household. UCs and villages/camps are selected on basis of Afghan and Host communities\' availability as well as access and security convenience. One Tehsil and Two UCs were selected at time of design however at the time of data collection, it was observed that 1 Tehsil and 3 UCs were covered from districts Killa Saifullah, Loralai and Pishin, for Quetta 2 tehsils and 4 UCs were covered in Quetta during MSRNA.', '1721804545_Screenshot 2024-07-24 120133.png', '1721804545_ECHO-HIP 2024 Need Assessment Report (240129) - ACCM Cleaned Version.pdf', 12, 1, '2024-02-01 10:54:28', '2024-07-24 07:02:26'),
(29, 'Baseline and Research Study', 'Development', 2, '[\"1\",\"2\"]', '[\"3\"]', '[\"68\"]', 'Completed', 0, 'Reasrch Study', 'Save the Children Pakistan envisages accomplishing “children’s safety and wellbeing improved through community-based integrated case management supported by enhanced access to safe schools and holistic services, and inclusion in social safety nets” by implementing four connected outcomes:\r\nOutcome 1: Access to safe schools enhanced for children of host and refugee communities.   \r\nOutcome 2: Access to CP holistic services enhanced for children of host and refugee communities. Outcome \r\nOutcome 3: Inclusion in social safety nets improved for families of host and refugee communities. \r\nOutcome 4: Effectiveness of the CICM model tested and evidence generated to disseminate with stakeholders for scale-up.', '1721806720_Screenshot 2024-07-24 123822.png', '1721806720_CONNECT II Baseline Snapshot 06.12.23.pptx', 12, 1, '2024-02-01 11:07:20', '2024-07-24 07:38:40'),
(30, 'Endline Evaluation', 'Development', 2, '[\"1\",\"2\"]', '[\"3\"]', '[\"170\"]', 'Completed', 0, 'Evaluation', 'The SCI’s Community-Level Integrated Case Management approach (CONNECT project) has adopted three core steps including identifying vulnerable children, providing individual child protection case management and ongoing support. The overall purpose of the CONNECT project is to: (i) Evidence whether integrated approaches are successful in getting children safely back into school and learning, along with improving children\'s well-being; (ii) Help refine the best implementation approaches based on learnings and data; (iii) Identify key challenges within the model so that we can address key barriers to effective Integration; and (iv) Ensure a pathway to scale through being able to apply the Community-level Integrated Case Management Model in different contexts across the SCI movement, with proven results. Besides, the outcomes of the CONNECT project are as follows: outcome 1- access to safe schools enhanced for children of host and refugee communities; outcome 2- access to CP holistic services enhanced for children of host and refugee communities; and outcome 3- inclusion in social safety nets improved for families of host and refugee communities. The overall purpose of the project is for children\'s safety and well-being to improve through community-based integrated case management supported by enhanced access to safe schools and holistic services, and inclusion in social safety nets.', '1721806460_Screenshot 2024-07-24 123356.png', '1721806460_CONNECT - Pakistan - Evaluation Report (230320) Final.pdf', 12, 1, '2024-02-01 11:10:11', '2024-07-24 07:34:20'),
