(49, 'Impact of Cross Functional Engagement on Employee\'s Satisfaction and Performance', NULL, NULL, 'null', 'null', 'null', NULL, 1, NULL, 'The objective of this survey was to analyze the impact of cross-functional engagement on employee\r\nperformance and overall job satisfaction within the organization. This survey was conducted to gather\r\ninsights from all staff members, irrespective of their current involvement in cross-functional roles, aiming to\r\nunderstand the broader implications of collaborative efforts on employee experience against one of the\r\nlearning questions of country learning agenda (CLA) i.e., “Does cross-functional engagement across project\r\nmanagement functions enhance employee performance and satisfaction?”. The data was collected using\r\nan online survey digitized in SCI Kobo toolbox, reflecting the genuine feedback of staff members', '1724918004_MicrosoftTeams-image (2).png', '1724918004_Cross Functional Engagement Survey Report (240529)_Clean Version_Final.pdf', 12, NULL, '2024-08-29 07:53:24', '2024-08-29 07:53:24'),
(50, 'Life-Saving Health, Nutrition and Child Protection Support to Afghan Refugees and Host Communities In Balochistan Province, Pakistan', 'Humanitarian', 46, '[\"4\",\"1\"]', '[\"3\"]', '[\"68\",\"75\"]', 'Completed', 0, 'Assessment', 'Save the Children International (Pakistan) GFFO-funded project, working in District Pishin and Killa Abdullah, Balochistan, focused on enhancing community healthcare while targeting health, nutrition, and child protection sectors. This collaborative effort aims to reach over 79,123 beneficiaries, prioritizing vulnerable groups like Pregnant and Lactating Women (PLWs), People with Disabilities (PWDs), and children. The purpose of the baseline assessment is to establish effective project planning, setting benchmarks aiding ongoing monitoring and offering actionable recommendations based on key findings. The initiative concentrates on strengthening community-based child protection mechanisms, including MHPSS, alongside local implementing partner and government departments at district and provincial levels. Engagement with local communities and their representative groups ensures participatory, people-centered approaches, aligning interventions with stakeholders like United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) and the government of Balochistan for coordination and complementarity within the region.', '1724922512_MicrosoftTeams-image (2).png', '1724922513_GFFO Baseline Assessment Report.pdf', 12, NULL, '2024-08-29 09:08:33', '2024-08-29 09:08:33');
