(390, '1', 'obs', 'It was observed that government department has given another rehab contract to UN-Habitat. The contractor of UN-Habitat started dismantling the plaster work to start the renovation of the same classroom which was already rehabilitated by Save the Children before 30th March 2024. The school was last time visited by SCI Field Engineer in the 2nd week of March and deadline for some rectification work was 25th of March 2024. The SRSP field engineer achieved all the action points suggested by SCI field engineer before 30th March 2024. The contractor started the work from 3rd May 2024. The twin latrines recently constructed are being used as storeroom by contractor for new renovation work. \r\nIt indicates poor coordination with government education department by SCI/SRSP as the funds were wasted due to duplication of funding from two international funding agencies. The funds could have been better utilized in the rehabilitation of any other flood affected school by regular coordination with district education department.', 'Not Fully Met', 'It was observed that government department has given another rehab contract to UN-Habitat. The contractor of UN-Habitat started dismantling the plaster work to start the renovation of the same classroom which was already rehabilitated by Save the Children before 30th March 2024. The school was last time visited by SCI Field Engineer in the 2nd week of March and deadline for some rectification work was 25th of March 2024. The SRSP field engineer achieved all the action points suggested by SCI field engineer before 30th March 2024. The contractor started the work from 3rd May 2024. The twin latrines recently constructed are being used as storeroom by contractor for new renovation work. \r\nIt indicates poor coordination with government education department by SCI/SRSP as the funds were wasted due to duplication of funding from two international funding agencies. The funds could have been better utilized in the rehabil