(304, 72, 'KP-26', 'obs', 'TLC Tent was repaired after it was partially damaged by snowfall during winter. The tent was reinstalled with wooden supports which might be unsafe for children.', 'Since the elbows and joints were broken and alternate similar parts were not available in the market, therefore the broken parts were repaired, and some were replaced by making new from local wielders. To protect the tents from further damage, wooden supports were installed for additional safety of tents. However, the wooden supports/pillars will be replaced with steel frame pillars.\nIn future, it is recommended that customized tents should be made with steel pillars in the centre as the current tents were lacking that essential pillar in the centre. The vendour may be asked to provide some additional elbows and joints to be replaced in case of such emergency. Secondly the winterized school tents should be provided for establishing TLC or CFS in future to avoid water seepage due to rain or snowfall.\nWooden Pillars have been replaced with steel frame pillars.', 'SRSP/Facilitato', '2023-05-15', 'Acheived', '2023-05-15', 'Wooden Pillars have been replaced with steel frame pillars.', '', 'Usama Qayyum', '2023-12-11 19:00:00'),
