(292, 72, 'KP-26', 'obs', 'TLC was also assessed by SRSP under DEC II for school rehab activities. But this school may not be considered for school rehab as its not flood affected. Secondly the school needs minor repair work of CGI sheets on roof which government may manage from annual maintenance budget.', 'Decision about school rehabilitation will be sought from senior management of SRSP and SCI. The decision will be communicated afterwards.    \"The criteria for establishment of TLC is : 1): School building is included in fully/partially damaged list from the education department, 2): Boundary wall is damaged or there is a water seepage/leakage from any side including roof, 3): walls or roof is fully/partially damaged, 4): WASH Facility is damaged or nonfunctional, 5): infrastructure is damage by rain flood, 6): vulnerable to land sliding or rain flood.\nThe TLC was established after school assessment based on six-point criteria and it was found vulnerable. The action point is not applicable. \nThe above criteria was finalized  by the SCI and SRSP management. In light of above the rehabilitation of GPS Chancharay meet the criteria.\"\n', 'SRSP/Facilitato', '2023-08-05', 'Acheived', '2023-05-08', 'The criteria for establishment of TLC is : 1): School building is included in fully/partially damaged list from the education department, 2): Boundary wall is damaged or there is a water seepage/leakage from any side including roof, 3): walls or roof is fully/partially damaged, 4): WASH Facility is damaged or nonfunctional, 5): infrastructure is damage by rain flood, 6): vulnerable to land sliding or rain flood.\nThe TLC was established after school assessment based on six-point criteria and it was found vulnerable. The action point is not applicable.\nThe above criteria was finalized  by the SCI and SRSP management. In light of above the rehabilitation of GPS Chancharay meet the criteria.', '', 'Usama Qayyum', '2023-12-11 19:00:00'),
