(570, 'SRSP project manager formed a team, which comprised Zahid Ali Khan MEAL officer, and Muhammad Fawad Project Officer of SRSP district swat to probe the issue. Mr. Fazal Nawab (complainant) is the elder brother of Muhammad Israr and both live in one house in a joint family. Both the brothers are skilled laborers and it is known to everyone in the village. Muhammad Israr was assessed as a skilled laborer under the CFW scheme of Sotal Bagh (Tiraat North) and he worked on-site for 6 days from 13 Jan to 18th Jan 2024, and then he got sick and was unable to work. Therefore the village committee decided to replace him with his own brother named Fazal Nawab for rest of the days. Fazal Nawab was called and he agreed to complete the remaining 6 days\' work as per the terms and conditions on which his brother Muhammad Israr was assessed and hired for 12 days as a skilled laborer @ PKR-1800 per day. The food basket of PKR-21,600 was received by Muhammad Israr on his own name’s registered mobile number, 0346-5364910, and his CNIC #15602-04070695 and dully verified and confirmed from the Finance section as well. Mr. Israr was of the view that his elder brother Fazal Nawab is responsible for running home expenses and I have handed over the PKR-21,600 to him, as he manages the home\'s monthly food requirement, Muhammad Israr further expressed his bond with his brother Fazal Nawaz. The community resolution and meeting minutes available along with SRSP report. The action point well taken.', '2024-03-26', 1456, 'Close', 4, '2024-05-08 05:54:35', '2024-05-08 05:54:35'),
