(778, 'The Project Manager SRSP shared that We had a meeting with contractors on 7, Aug-2024 stressing to expedite the work on all sites to meet the deadline. It was assured by the contractors to increase labour numbers and we are having follow ups on this. We will be able to complete the rehab work of GPS Bayoun Kalam till 15, Aug-2024.\r\n\r\nLearning and Education kits were provided to current phase\'s 8 schools before summer vocations. There are four schools left namely; GPS Garilagan, GPS Bayoun Kalam, GPS Ashoran, and GGPS Kwaro Tangy. They have been planned to be provided Education and Learning kits between 12 to 16, Aug-2024. Please be noted all children enrolled after kits distribution in the earlier 8 schools, will also receive learning kits as part of the plan. The complaint was closed based on the action taken by partner.', '2024-08-09', 1841, 'Close', 4, '2024-08-15 09:43:24', '2024-08-15 09:43:24'),
(779, 'As per Abdul Sami\'s recent reply, The tank is not functional because the task-related work to the tank has been not completed yet. An email has been sent to NRSP regarding this issue, and they are responsible for completing the work on the tank. Once the tank work is finished, Community people will be able to start getting water from the tank.', '2024-08-15', 1745, 'Open', 103, '2024-08-15 09:45:31', '2024-08-15 09:45:31'),
(780, 'The Project Manager SRSP responded that currently we have no availability of budget for the provision of more school tents. Last time in June 2023, the education department shared that the school will be shifted to any other safe place as the area is flood prone and there are more chances of land sliding. SRSP already informed the school management that the tents should be uninstalled as their life is over.\"', '2024-08-09', 1842, 'Close', 4, '2024-08-15 09:52:02', '2024-08-15 09:52:02'),
(781, 'As per Abdul Sami\'s recent reply, The tank is not functional because the task-related work to the tank has been not completed yet. An email has been sent to NRSP regarding this issue, and they are responsible for completing the work on the tank. Once the tank work is finished, Community people will be able to start getting water from the tank.', '2024-08-15', 1743, 'Open', 103, '2024-08-15 09:54:33', '2024-08-15 09:54:33');
