(4, '2023-09-11', '17091-Hotline-49/Aain Ashoka', 'Saba Saeed', 'Close', '2', '49', '5', 'Mankiyal', 'Aain Ashoka', '3', 'Muhammad Hussain', 'Yes', 'Male', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Direct Beneficiary', '03429281764', 'I am the chairman of the child protection committee. The SRSP has hired a contractor to complete the GPS Aain Ashoka rehabilitation work. The contractor \"Nawab Syed\" visited the school two weeks before. He stated that we will begin work in a few days. After a week, another person named \"Usman Shah\" arrived with a few workers and identified himself as a contractor. I requested that the contractor\'s name be Nawab Syed. He stated that he had given me this contract. They dumped construction materials (Bajri) inside the school. When we called Usman Shah again after a week, he said we would be there in 2-3 days to begin the work.  Now, another local contractor visited the school yesterday and informed me that Usman Shah had given me the contract and that we would complete the work. i wanted to ask, how will the school rehabilitation work be finished if things continue in this manner? And how will the quality of work be ensured if the contractors continue to engage other contractors in order to save money?', '1', 'we forwarded this complaint to the partner and technical WASH coordinator.', 'School rehabilitation', '5', NULL, '6', 'Yes', NULL, 'Abid ur Rehman', 'WASH Coordinator- KP', NULL, '2023-09-11', NULL, '2023-09-19', '', NULL, 8, NULL, 7, '2023-09-11 04:13:08', 7, '2023-10-19 04:54:24', 7, '2023-09-19 11:06:05'),
(1020, '2023-10-18', '1019-1697712424', 'Sanam Altaf', 'Close', '4', '168', '35', '48', 'Rabani Muhalla', '10', 'Ameeran', 'Yes', 'Female', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Direct Beneficiary', '03194724037', 'A complaint received via hotline from Rehmani Muhalla, it states” I received the hygiene kit distributed by SCI and I found some items missing in it [1. Shampoo 2. Soap 3. Laundry soaps (only received 4 soaps, in total there were 8 soaps)] I conformed my kit with my neighbor’s kit, and I discovered items are missing in my kit, so please check and provide me all remaining items”.', '1', 'Complaint shared with relevant department to investigate and response to the query.', 'Hygiene Kit Distribution (MPCA)', '4', NULL, '6', 'Yes', NULL, 'Muhammad Fazil', 'Senior WASH Coordinator', NULL, '2023-10-18', NULL, '2023-10-30', 'Satisfied', NULL, NULL, 'SCI Team conducted physical counting and verification of remaining hygiene kit’ items in all three districts, along with IP and noted that No missing items reported from any of the district and all items found in accordance with approved specs and quantity given in PO. Quality of items also found satisfactory and uniform. So, it seems that missing items issue is happening during transportation of kits to field, load/unload, as some of kits packing found damaged or rotten. For future distribution now onward IP is advised to display the list of hygiene items at each distribution point and ensure that all beneficiaries have been oriented about the number of items in local language and confirmation of receiving of all items as per list before beneficiaries leave the site.', 13, '2023-10-19 06:12:25', NULL, '2023-11-07 07:59:01', NULL, NULL),
(5, '2023-09-11', '71132-Hotline-49/Amlok Bagh', 'Saba Saeed', 'Close', '2', '49', 'Bahrain', 'Madyen', 'Amlok Bagh', '3', 'Nawab Ali', 'Yes', 'Male', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Direct Beneficiary', '03453754109', 'I am a CPC chairman at GPS Amlok Bagh. The SRSP has already notified us that when the rehabilitation work begins, the contractor will coordinate with the school staff and the CPC committee regarding the construction. SRSP further informed us that CPC members will be responsible for overseeing the rehab work. The rehabilitation work at GPS Amlok Bagh has now begun without any consultation with the CPC members or school staff. The school had a space that needed to be excavated. However, work on the washrooms near the veranda where students sit for classes has begun.', '1', NULL, 'School Rehablitation', '4', '', '6', 'Yes', NULL, 'Ejaz Shah', 'MEAL Manager', NULL, '2023-09-11', NULL, '2023-09-20', 'Satisfied', NULL, 9, NULL, 7, '2023-09-11 05:28:51', 7, '2023-10-03 04:41:52', 7, '2023-10-03 10:58:06'),
