(74, '2023-08-29', '925-Feedback Form (8/2023) Swat /Kot Charbagh', 'Ejaz Shah', 'Close', '2', '49', 'Charbagh', 'Kot Charbagh', 'Kot Charbagh', '3', 'Nusrat Bibi', 'No', 'Female', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Direct Beneficiary', '', 'the training is very good and informative. i like the venue and food of the training.', '3', '', 'Teachers Training', '1', '', '2', 'No', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Satisfied', '', NULL, '', 11, '2023-09-11 05:28:51', 7, '2023-09-28 10:35:08', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(75, '2023-08-30', '926-Feedback Form (8/2023) Swat/Barn Qandeel', 'Ejaz Shah', 'Close', '2', '49', '5', 'Teraat', 'Barn Qandeel', '3', 'Syed Asad Imran', 'No', 'Male', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Non-beneficiary', '', 'the analogue weight scale is required to record the weight of the patients. The existing digital weight scale requires smooth and solid surface to measure the exact weight. so if analogue weight scale provided it would be of much benefit of the patient. the alternate male/female doctor should be arranged as a backup support in case of emergency leave by staff. Triage Trained staff should be hired to facilitate the OPD and avoid overcrowding. Some visiting people waste our time even though they are not suffering from any disease but still insist for checkup and medicines.', '3', '', 'Static Health Facility', '4', '', '4', 'Yes', '', 'Syed Sajjad', 'Project Manager SRSP', '', '2023-09-01', '', '2023-10-15', 'Satisfied', NULL, 44, '', 11, '2023-09-11 05:28:51', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 7, '2023-10-05 10:44:01'),
(76, '2023-08-31', '927-Feedback Form (8/2023) Dadu/Muhammad Urs Leghari', 'Fatima Shahani', 'Close', '4', '100', 'Johi', 'Wahi Pandhi', 'Muhammad Urs Leghari', '10', 'Qurban Ali', 'Yes', 'Male', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Non-beneficiary', '03103344127', 'I am the VC president of this village, I have been the part of all the assessment conducted in the village. All the beneficiaries who recieved the assisstance are satisfied & thankful to the organization. Further I request to provide assisstance for the remaining vulnerable HHs if it is possible.', '3', '', 'Buisness restoration assessment planning', '3', '', '3', 'Yes', '', 'Aliman Shah', 'FSL Manager', NULL, '2023-09-01', NULL, '2023-09-04', 'Satisfied', '', NULL, 'Beneficiary was guided well that there is a proper criterion to select any beneficiary so if anyone not meeting the selection criteria will not be considered for any assistance.', 11, '2023-09-11 05:28:51', 13, '2023-11-17 10:59:28', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(77, '2023-08-31', '928-Feedback Form (8/2023) Dadu/Muhammad Urs Leghari', 'Fatima Shahani', 'Close', '4', '100', 'Johi', 'Wahi Pandhi', 'Muhammad Urs Leghari', '10', 'Shaharbano', 'Yes', 'Female', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Direct Beneficiary', '03423921660', 'She requested to release the assisstance for restoration of small business as she could restore her business as soon as possible.', '3', '', 'Buisness restoration assessment planning', '3', '', '3', 'Yes', '', 'Aliman Shah', 'FSL Manager', NULL, '2023-09-01', NULL, '2023-09-04', 'Satisfied', '', NULL, 'Complainant was told that there is a mechanism to be followed for every assessment, and verification process takes time, after verification from different departments payments are disbursed so it will take some time.', 11, '2023-09-11 05:28:51', 13, '2023-10-30 06:21:47', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(78, '2023-09-07', '929-Hotline  (7/2023) Swat/Aain Ashoka', 'Saba Saeed', 'Close', '2', '49', '5', 'Mankiyal', 'Aain Ashoka', '3', 'Zia ul Haq', 'Yes', 'Male', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Direct Beneficiary', '03452114100', 'I am the PST teacher at GPS Ashoka. SRSP selected our school for the rehabilitation work. It had previously been decided that the SRSP will build 2 classrooms for the school. However, since the rehabilitation work has begun, they have told us they will only build one classroom. At the back of our school, there is an appropriate place for the classroom. We asked the SRSP officials to build the classroom on the back side, but they informed us that they had no funding provided for?excavation. The classroom will be built by the SRSP?in the school\'s playground. Since the classroom is?26 by 15, there won\'t be any space for students to play or gather for an assembly. I would like to request that your organization build the classroom towards the back side of school, so that the school\'s play area won\'t be damaged.', '1', 'serious notice was taken by DCD, MEAL Specialist, and Shelter & WASH Advisor. it was advised to the area director that necessary action should be taken to resolve this issue.', 'Rehablitation of School', '5', NULL, '5', 'Yes', '', 'Ejaz Shah', 'MEAL Manager', '', '2023-09-07', '', '2023-09-30', 'Satisfied', NULL, 12, 'it was confirmed by the field engineer of SCI, that the playground was kept intact and room construction was on the back side of the school. Also, the MEAL manager had a face-to-face discussion with the complainant and it was agreed by the complainant that there is no other space available for the construction of the classroom. therefore the existing play area will not be disturbed and the selected place for the classroom is agreed upon.', 11, '2023-09-11 05:28:51', 7, '2023-10-19 04:43:44', 7, '2023-09-19 10:53:04'),
(79, '2023-09-07', '930-Hotline  (7/2023) Swat/Barshagram', 'Saba Saeed', 'Close', '2', '49', '5', 'Terat', 'Barshagram', '3', 'Asiya', 'Yes', 'Female', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Indirect Beneficiary', '03469434707', 'I am a teacher of GGPS Barshagram. The SRSP staff created a committee in the month of July and included my daughter (age 19 years) Haseena and seven other women in it. I received a call from an SRSP official the day before yesterday asking me to contact every committee member for the training. I contacted every committee member. All of the committee members arrived up on the scheduled training day. my daughter and another female committee member were not allowed to attend the training. When we inquired, the staff told us that just 6 members would be taking part in the training. If so, i wanted to know why they added both of them to the committee. Additionally, the SRSP staff needed to let me know in advance not to call both of them so they wouldn\'t came up for the training. according to the pictures provided by teacher, shows that the both of them were part of the committee.\nSecond, the refreshments that SRSP usually provides after sessions or meetings are not of good quality. As some of the children were suffered from stomach upset after eating that meal. ', '1', '', 'CPC Training', '7', '25266', '1', 'Yes', '', '', '', '', '2023-09-07', '', '2024-02-13', 'Partially Satisfied', '', NULL, 'Substantiated Closed', 11, '2023-09-11 05:28:51', 0, '2024-02-13 10:53:39', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(80, '2023-09-07', '931-Hotline  (7/2023) Swat/Damana', 'Saba Saeed', 'Close', '2', '49', '5', 'Terat', 'Damana', 'HUM II', 'Sarwat', 'Yes', 'Female', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Direct Beneficiary', '03409429465', 'I am a social activist of Damana village UC Terat. i have come to know from my own resources, that the SRSP staff has conducted assessment for any Kitchen gardening scheme in some villages of UC Terat. I contacted the SRSP team, and they informed me that we will also be conducting assessments in Damana village. Later, the team informed me that the social welfare committee in Damana had just been formed by SRSP. upon probing this matter, I learnt that the SRSP team?has?formed the?Social Welfare committee by the name of Damana?at the residence of a social activist at village Terat. I have received confirmation from my village community members that local residents of village Damana?were not consulted for this assessment by the SRSP team. My biggest concern is how the Social Welfare Committee was established without consulting the actual community of village Damana. Though our village is affected by flood and kitchen gardening assistance is highly required by the community.', '1', '', 'Conditional Cash Assistance', '5', '', '3', 'Yes', '', '', '', '', '2023-09-07', '', '2023-10-05', 'Satisfied', NULL, 28, '', 11, '2023-09-11 05:28:51', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 7, '2023-10-05 10:21:12'),
(81, '2023-09-07', '932-Hotline  (7/2023) Swat/Baralai', 'Saba Saeed', 'Close', '2', '49', '5', 'Madyen', 'Baralai', '', 'Taj Muhammad', 'Yes', 'Male', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Indirect Beneficiary', '03439395255', 'I am a community Saddar of the village Baralai. The residents of the village benefited greatly from the medical health camp that SRSP organized at Village Baralai last month. The free medical care and medication were greatly appreciated. I therefore request that kindly arrange the medical camp in our village once more this month.', '1', 'SRSP staff thanked the caller for appreciating the mobile health camp. However, since the mobile health camp is planned for three days at one particular place and most of the community was already provided the health support in that village, therefore we are not able to extend the mobile health camp for one more day. The same response communicated to the caller and he was satisfied.', 'Medical Health Camp', '3', '', '4', 'Yes', '', 'Syed Sajjad', 'Project Manager SRSP', NULL, '2023-09-07', NULL, '2023-09-07', 'Satisfied', NULL, 0, '', 11, '2023-09-11 05:28:51', 7, '2023-09-18 05:41:57', 7, '2023-09-18 05:43:06'),
(84, '2023-07-17', '806-HotLine (7/2023) khairpur/Muhammad Punhal', 'Sanam Altaf', 'Close', '4', '168', 'Thari Mir Wah', 'Hindyari', 'Muhammad Punhal', '8', 'Sabir Ali', 'Yes', 'Male', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Indirect Beneficiary', '03252348752', 'Sabir Ali called and requested for assisstance (CNIC Correction) he stated his mother was selected for MPCA and her name is also mentioned in selected beneficiaries however her there is an error of a digit  in her CNIC in final list of cash utilization report, due to which she is unable to receive her cash, as system is biometric based and can only be verified by correct CNIC.', '1', 'Caller was asked to get CNIC checked again, after checking CNIC again from the database it was come to know there was error in the one digit, caller was ensured the correction within sometime, meanwhile feedback was shared FSL manger for timely correction. ', 'MPCA ', '3', NULL, '3', 'Yes', NULL, 'Aliman Shah', 'FSL Manager ', NULL, '2023-07-17', NULL, '2023-07-18', 'Satisfied', NULL, 1, NULL, 1, '2023-09-12 11:32:33', 1, '2023-09-12 11:32:33', 13, '2023-10-05 11:55:01'),
