(116, '2023-07-17', '779-Hotline  (7/2023) Swat/Liakot', 'Ejaz Shah', 'Close', '2', '49', 'Balakot', '', 'Liakot', '3', 'XXX', 'No', 'Male', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Direct Beneficiary', '', 'The complainant said that \"I have come to BHU Liakot for medical checkup but no staff and medicines are available at BHU Liakot.\" ', '1', 'The complaint was shared with SRSP Program Manager without disclosing the name of complainant. Partner staff informed that BHU was open with OPD of 60 patients. According to MO (Dr. Shahwaliullah) the BHU staff was present including one Medical Officer Male and one Medical Officer Female and one Dispenser (Pharmacist). However the Female Psychologist and Nutritionist were absent without leave application. The N utritionist joined in the first week of July but she was absent for last one week as per MO. The MO also shared live location and scanned copy of attendance record of staff present at BHU. It was communicated to the complainant that \"BHU was open and health staff was present with OPD of 60 patients\" but the complainant was not satisfied with the response He still claimed that the staff rushed towards the BHU Liakot after his complaint. The complainant reinforced on oath that the staff was not present at the facility and came after the complaint.\nOn 10/8/2023 MEAL Manager met the complainant and recorded feedback on the standard feedback form. The complainant recorded the same statement. According to complainant “He went to BHU at 1:35 PM and found the SRSP health staff absent. He inquired from the government dispenser about their absence and he was informed that the SRSP staff left half an hour before official closing time. According to the complainant, the staff came back at 1:45PM (within 10 minutes) after his complaint on hotline number as they were residing in the nearby hotel. Upon probing about any other witness available in the area, the complainant said there were two other male community members who witnessed but they didn’t want to complain. The complainant was also probed about frequency of staff absence, he informed that it happened only once. \nAccording to Project Manager SRSP, there were some issues of government dispenser with SRSP health facility staff, therefore, he must have made this case through community complainant. \nTherefore, due to absence of enough evidence regarding the complaint, the complaint is being closed. The SRSP Project Manager has already instructed the health facility staff to share their live location/SMS with him and Dr. Shahab (Health Coordinator) at the time of their arrival and departure to avoid such problem in future. Dr. Shahab was also advised by SRSP Project Manager to check the staff attendance regularly on daily basis by call/SMS to confirm staff availability at the site.\nHowever, the complainant wass informed that he should contact through hotline number in case it happens again in future.', 'Static Health Facility', '5', '', '4', 'Yes', '', 'Sayyed Sajjad and SCI senior management.', 'Program Manager SRSP, DCD, Director PQEI, AD and H', '', '2023-07-17', '', '2023-07-20', 'Satisfied', '', 3, '', 11, '2023-09-11 05:28:51', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
