(272, '2022-10-05', '21-Hotline (10/2022) Swat/Rustamabad, Gabral', 'Ejaz Shah', 'Close', '2', '49', '5', 'Utror', 'Rustamabad, Gabral', '20', 'Suleman Khan S/O Aurangzeb Khan', 'Yes', 'Male', '19-50 years', '', 'Direct Beneficiary', '0346-9157994', '\"I am not being given \'rashan\' (Food and NFI) by SRSP staff at distribution point \'Atrore\'. My house was fully damaged by flood and I am not able to manage my family needs\"', '1', 'It was informed by SRSP focal person that \"We get the approved and verified list from Assistant Commissioner and include only those community persons whos names are in the list. The community members having fully damaged house are given preference for Food, NFI and Shelter distribution. 2nd priority is given to those having partially damaged houses. The procedure of community registeration is that all affected persons report their damages to local police station and after verification by police, they are referred to local Tehsildar to get registered as flood affectee on the basis of house being fully/partially damaged by the flood. The complete list is available with Tehsil Assistant Commissioner which is available to any NGO/organization/general-public upon request. With limited resources its not possible for any organization to conduct door-to-door assessment for which NOC is required by government.\". The response communicated to the complainant and he agreed to get registered as per the procedure communicated by SRSP.', 'Food Aid Distribution', '3', '', '3', 'Yes', '', 'Syed Muhammad Sajjad', ' MEAL Focal person SRSP', '', '2022-10-05', 'Closed Timely', '2022-10-05', 'Satisfied', '', 0, '', 1, '2023-09-26 14:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
