(279, '2022-10-27', '28-Hotline (10/2022) Swat/Madyan', 'Ejaz Shah', 'Close', '2', '49', '4', 'Madyan', 'Madyan', '20', 'Syed Salahuddin', 'Yes', 'Male', '19-50 years', '', 'Direct Beneficiary', '0343-2987268', '\"My house was damaged during the current flood. My house was under construction without the roof. I was living in another village (Garahi). But later my underconstruction house was demolished and fully destroyed by recent flood. I received support from other organizations and local philanthropists but no support was provided by SRSP. I need cash or 5 items.\"', '1', 'The request for assistance communicated to SRSP focal person and he informed that they will contact the person and will consider him for food/5 assistance based on preliminary assessment by SRSP staff. \n\nDated:18/11/22: SRSP informed that the respondent was re-assessed but his house was underconstruction (not dewelled) which was damaged by flood. He was residing in his another house in another village. He was told that does not fulfil the criteria of fully damaged dewelled house, where the household is living. He was satisfied with the response from SRSP.', 'Food Aid Distribution', '3', '', '3', 'Yes', '', 'Syed Sajjad', 'Project Coordinator SRSP', '', '2022-11-19', 'Closed Timely', '2022-11-19', 'Satisfied', '', 0, '', 1, '2023-09-26 14:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(280, '2022-10-27', '29-Hotline (10/2022) Swat/Saatal', 'Ejaz Shah', 'Close', '2', '49', '4', 'Bahrain', 'Saatal', '9', 'Islam Uddin', 'Yes', 'Male', '19-50 years', '', 'Indirect Beneficiary', '0342-9666924', '\"Islam uddin is a person with speaking disability. He is very poor and needs food assistance. His CNIC is 15602-2148534-9\", this was communicated by Syed Salahuddin on hotline number.', '1', 'The request for assistance communicated to SRSP focal person and he informed that they will contact the person and will consider him for food assistance based on preliminary assessment by SRSP staff.\n\nDated: 7/11/22, SRSP was contacted again for the updates, they shared that the respondent Islam uddin is not effected by flood but he is poor and PWD (not able to speak), based on his poverty and disability SRSP decided to give him hygiene kit. The respondents\'s nephew(Fawad Khan 0347 9426815) was informed with the SRSP response and he was satisfied. 19/11/22: SRSP (Mr. Sajjad) shared that he will be provided hygiene kit within next 3 days, the same response was communicated to Mr. Fawad Khan and he was satisfied.', 'Food Aid Distribution', '3', '', '3', 'Yes', '', 'Syed Sajjad', 'Project Coordinator SRSP', '', '2022-11-19', 'Closed with Delay', '2022-11-19', 'Satisfied', '', 0, '', 1, '2023-09-26 14:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(281, '2022-11-07', '30-Hotline (11/2022) Swat/Kedam', 'Ejaz Shah', 'Close', '2', '49', '5', 'Balakot', 'Kedam', '20', 'Sohail Khan', 'Yes', 'Male', '19-50 years', '', 'Indirect Beneficiary', '0310-2304388', '\"Thank you for providing health services in our area. We appreciate the health services provided by Save the Children and SRSP staff in our area. Many community members including men, women and children are getting these services and medicines with your support otherwise it would have been very difficult for the community to access health services far from their homes due to time and financial constraints. Positive feedback about Save the Children provided services of health camp shared with SRSP focal Person along with the regular complaint about unavailability of medicines related to skin allergies, sugar and blood pressure. The project coordinator SRSP informed that \"I will request relevant health focal point of Save the Children to see if these medicines can be provided to health camp\". The caller was informed that your concern about unavailability of medicines related to skin allergies, sugar and blood pressure has been communicated to relevant department and further update will be shared soon with the caller. \n\nOn 18/11/22, Dr Waleed (Health Advisor) responded that \"We are due to receive Permethrin from the vendor for the treatment of Scabies. Once available we’ll send it forward for the MHT use. For diabetes, the available medicines should be used for refill of already diagnosed patients; who are already on treatment with available prescription slips. The MHTs doctors should avoid new diagnosis to the extent possible.\nFor glucometers, we don’t have them available in our supplies. The strips could be quite expensive and we don’t have funds to cover those. If needed, the patient should be requested to do the tests privately.\" the same response was communicated to callers and they were satisfied.e', '1', 'Positive fedback about Save the Children provided services of health camp shared with SRSP focal Person along with the regular complaint about unavailability of medicines related to skin allergies, sugar and blood pressure. The project coordinator SRSP informed that \"I will request relevant health focal point of Save the Children to see if these medicines can be provided to health camp\". The caller was informed that your concern about unavailability of medicines related to skin allergies, sugar and blood pressure has been communicated to relevant department and further update will be shared soon with the caller.\n\nOn 18/11/22, Dr Waleed (Health Advisor) responded that \"We are due to receive Permethrin from the vendor for the treatment of Scabies. Once available we’ll send it forward for the MHT use. For diabetes, the available medicines should be used for refill of already diagnosed patients; who are already on treatment with available prescription slips. The MHTs doctors should avoid new diagnosis to the extent possible.\n\nFor glucometers, we don’t have them available in our supplies. The strips could be quite expensive and we don’t have funds to cover those. If needed, the patient should be requested to do the tests privately.\" the same response was communicated to callers and they were satisfied.', 'Thematic Intervention', '5', '', '4', 'Yes', '', 'Syed Muhammad Sajjad', 'Project Coordinator SRSP', '', '2022-11-19', 'Closed with Delay', '2022-11-19', 'Satisfied', '', 0, '', 1, '2023-09-26 14:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(282, '2022-11-07', '31-Hotline (11/2022) Swat/Torwal, Kedam', 'Ejaz Shah', 'Close', '2', '49', '5', 'Balakot', 'Torwal, Kedam', '20', 'Bakht Zameen', 'Yes', 'Male', '19-50 years', '', 'Indirect Beneficiary', '0311-3367099', '\"Thank you for providing health services in our area. We appreciate the health services provided by Save the Children and SRSP staff in our area. Many community members including men, women and children are getting these services and medicines with your support otherwise it would have been very difficult for the community to access health services far from their homes due to time and financial constraints. Positive feedback about Save the Children provided services of health camp shared with SRSP focal Person along with the regular complaint about unavailability of medicines related to skin allergies/skin problems. The project coordinator SRSP informed that \"I will request relevant health focal point of Save the Children to see if these medicines can be provided to health camp\".    On 18/11/22, Dr Waleed (Health Advisor) responded that \"We are due to receive Permethrin from the vendor for the treatment of skin allergies. Once available we’ll send it forward for the MHT use.', '1', 'Positive fedback about Save the Children provided services of health camp shared with SRSP focal Person along with the regular complaint about unavailability of medicines related to skin allergies/skin problems. The project coordinator SRSP informed that \"I will request relevant health focal point of Save the Children to see if these medicines can be provided to health camp\". The caller was informed that your concern about unavailability of medicines related to skin allergies has been communicated to relevant department and further update will be shared soon with the caller.\n\nOn 18/11/22, Dr Waleed (Health Advisor) responded that \"We are due to receive Permethrin from the vendor for the treatment of Scabies. Once available we’ll send it forward for the MHT use. For diabetes, the available medicines should be used for refill of already diagnosed patients; who are already on treatment with available prescription slips. The MHTs doctors should avoid new diagnosis to the extent possible.\n\nFor glucometers, we don’t have them available in our supplies. The strips could be quite expensive and we don’t have funds to cover those. If needed, the patient should be requested to do the tests privately.\" the same response was communicated to callers and they were satisfied.', 'Thematic Intervention', '5', '', '4', 'Yes', '', 'Syed Muhammad Sajjad', 'Project Coordinator SRSP', '', '2022-11-19', 'Closed Timely', '2022-11-19', 'Satisfied', '', 0, '', 1, '2023-09-26 14:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(283, '2022-11-07', '32-Hotline (11/2022) Swat/Kedam', 'Ejaz Shah', 'Close', '2', '49', '5', 'Balakot', 'Kedam', '20', 'Liaqat Ali', 'Yes', 'Male', '19-50 years', '', 'Indirect Beneficiary', '0312-9337088', '\"Thank you for providing health services in our area. We appreciate the health services provided by Save the Children and SRSP staff in our area. Many community members including men, women and children are getting these services and medicines with your support otherwise it would have been very difficult for the community to access health services far from their homes due to time and financial constraints. I just want to inform you that medicines related to scabies, skin diseases and allergies are not available at health camp. Kindly provide these medicines as these are needed by the community.\"\nOn 18/11/22, Dr Waleed (Health Advisor) responded that \"We are due to receive Permethrin from the vendor for the treatment of Scabies. Once available we’ll send it forward for the MHT use. For diabetes, the available medicines should be used for refill of already diagnosed patients; who are already on treatment with available prescription slips. The MHTs doctors should avoid new diagnosis to the extent possible.\n', '1', 'Positive fedback about Save the Children provided services of health camp shared with SRSP focal Person along with the regular complaint about unavailability of medicines related to scabies/skin problems. The project coordinator SRSP informed that \"I will request relevant health focal point of Save the Children to see if these medicines can be provided to health camp\". The caller was informed that your concern about unavailability of medicines related to scabies/skin problems has been communicated to relevant department and further update will be shared soon with the caller.\n\nOn 18/11/22, Dr Waleed (Health Advisor) responded that \"We are due to receive Permethrin from the vendor for the treatment of Scabies. Once available we’ll send it forward for the MHT use. For diabetes, the available medicines should be used for refill of already diagnosed patients; who are already on treatment with available prescription slips. The MHTs doctors should avoid new diagnosis to the extent possible.\n\nFor glucometers, we don’t have them available in our supplies. The strips could be quite expensive and we don’t have funds to cover those. If needed, the patient should be requested to do the tests privately.\" the same response was communicated to callers and they were satisfied.', 'Thematic Intervention', '5', '', '4', 'Yes', '', 'Syed Muhammad Sajjad', 'Project Coordinator SRSP', '', '2022-11-19', 'Closed with Delay', '2022-11-19', 'Satisfied', '', 0, '', 1, '2023-09-26 14:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
