(337, '2022-12-21', '86-Hotline (12/2022) Khairpur/Imam Bux Sheeno', 'Seema', 'Close', '4', '168', '5', 'Tali', 'Imam Bux Sheeno', '20', 'Naeem Ali Sheeno', 'Yes', 'Male', '19-50 years', '', 'Indirect Beneficiary', '0308-3101803', 'Our village is in UC Tali, but team refused us for any type of Household assessment. Complainant further shared that, team said that your village is not nominated/included for HH assessment. Kindly have a look on my issue and assessed my village.', '1', 'Community concern was shared with the IP team. According to the Project Manager LRF “As there is no blanket coverage of assessment within union council. We initially shortlisted the villages during village profiling and unfortunately respective could not get shortlisted. However, we will keep the request in our record for any future assessments” Response was communicated to the complainant. ', 'Assessment', '4', '', '5', 'Yes', '', 'Imran ', 'PM-IP', '', NULL, 'Closed with Delay', '2023-01-01', 'Satisfied', '', NULL, '', 1, '2023-09-26 14:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(338, '2022-12-21', '87-Feedback Form (12/2022) Dadu/Kalarai Chandio', 'Seema', 'Close', '4', '100', '5', 'Thalho', 'Kalarai Chandio', '20', 'Imdad Ali', 'Yes', 'Male', '19-50 years', '', 'Direct Beneficiary', '0341-3308848', 'The organisation did a good job in this situation, especially after the flood, but the Sindh government should focus on education and health. However, they did not work on it. As a teacher, I appreciate your organization\'s work that in this time you came to work for the poor students and make a Temporary Learning Center for the betterment of students\' future. The schools were closed after 6 months (2 months of heavy rain, 2 months of flooding, and 2 months of summer vacations). As a result, students\' education was lost; however, the establishment of TLC is beneficial to the students, and the organisation also provides one teacher for support, which is incridible. I\'m at a loss for words when it comes to organisation. We were able to start our school simply through organisational efforts, and students are now eager to attend.', '3', 'Positive Feedback shared with IP-LRF Focal Person', 'TLC', '1', '', '2', 'Yes', '', 'Imran ', 'PM-IP', '', NULL, 'Closed Timely', '2022-12-26', 'Satisfied', '', NULL, '', 1, '2023-09-26 14:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(339, '2022-12-21', '88-Feedback Form (12/2022) Dadu/Kalarai Chandio', 'Seema', 'Close', '4', '100', '5', 'Thalho', 'Kalarai Chandio', '20', 'Dilbar Ali', 'Yes', 'Boy', 'Less than 18 years', '', 'Direct Beneficiary', '0341-3942486', 'Our school wasn\'t clean prior to the TLC, but it is now; Our village and homes were damaged by flooding, so we needed sports equipment, warm clothes, and jackets. We also needed more copies, books, and stationery so that we could teach and build our village. I also wanted to be a judge, so this would help me. We are grateful to your team for visiting our village and creating TLC.', '3', 'Request for assisstance share with LRF Focal Person ', 'TLC', '3', '', '2', 'Yes', '', 'Imran ', 'PM-IP', '', NULL, 'Closed Timely', '2022-12-26', 'Satisfied', '', NULL, '', 1, '2023-09-26 14:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
