(368, '2023-01-03', '117-Hotline (1/2023) Khairpur/Yaar Muhammad Sheena', 'Seema ', 'Close', '4', '168', '5', 'Tali', 'Yaar Muhammad Sheena', '20', 'Aijaz Ali', 'Yes', 'Male', '19-50 years', '', 'Indirect Beneficiary', '0304-36215067', 'Your team conducted assessment at our village, however they only assessed rich/influence households and we (15-20 HH) living in open or tents/shelter with more damaged houses were not assessed even after asking the team to take our information, they only took picture but didn’t include us in the assessment process', '1', 'After receiving this complained MEAL team visited the respective & investigated the matter. It was learnt that the village is comprised of 120 Households, out of which 61 households were assessed.\n\nUpon desk review of assessment data, it was learnt that inclusion of multiple communities including Talpur, Sheeno and Hindus “16 HHs of minority” was ensured during the assessment.\nInitially MEAL team had an observation walk throughout the village and could not find 20 HH living in tents at the village as claimed by the complainant.\nMEAL team interacted with multiple community elders for verifying the claim of complainant regrading favoritism/assessing only rich HHs, none of the interacted community members endorsed such claim.\nMEAL team also investigated the claim of assessing rich HHs by verifying 10% of the total assessed HHs in respective village and found that claim was baseless.\nHowever, MEAL team found few vulnerable (5) Households in village which were not included in initial assessment. IP team has agreed to include identified HHs in assessment (During debrief meeting)\nCommunity was not very much clear about selection criteria (Inclusion & Exclusion), and mobilization gap was also observed during the visit.', 'Assessment ', '4', '', '5', 'Yes', '', 'Imran', 'PM-IP', '', NULL, 'Closed Timely', '2023-01-09', 'Satisfied', '', NULL, '', 1, '2023-09-26 14:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
