(1133, '2023-11-21', '1133-1700561006', 'Saba Saeed', 'Close', '2', '49', '5', '94', 'Ghus Pishmal', '3', 'Syed Munir', 'Yes', 'Male', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Direct Beneficiary', '03149739393', 'It was decided during the technical assessment that we would be provided with the repair of the storage tank, pipeline with a 2-inch diameter pipe, and construction of the main hole. The contractor used a 1.5-inch pipe instead of a 2-inch pipe. The 1.5-inch pipe doesn’t fulfill the water needs of the village. Also, the quality of the pipe is very poor which will be damaged in a few months. the contractor did not repair the storage tank and he has not constructed the main hole. Upon probing the contractor responded that I don’t have enough budget to fulfill community needs.', '1', 'the complaint was forwarded for the suitable action required to proceed.', 'Water Supply Scheme', '5', NULL, '6', 'Yes', NULL, 'Irfan Majeed', 'Head of MEAL', NULL, '2023-11-21', NULL, '2023-11-29', 'Satisfied', NULL, NULL, 'the complaint was shared with the Area Director and WASH focal point. later MEAL manager KP visited the site and met with the complainant and other village committee members. based on a detailed discussion with the village committee and complainant, it was learned that the community had a genuine concern. Therefore, with the support of the Area Director and WASH Advisor, the complaint was addressed by changing the diameter of the pipe from 50mm to 75mm. and the additional amount required for this change was arranged and allocated respectively. the response was shared with the complainant and he was very happy and satisfied.', 7, '2023-11-21 10:09:06', NULL, '2023-12-22 05:34:46', NULL, NULL),
