(1412, '2024-02-22', '1412-1709096971', 'Shahida Khaskheli', 'Close', '3', '178', '34', '86', 'Muhammad Panah Bughatti, Ward No. 26, Deh Barro 02, UC Judhair, Tehsil Jhatpat, District Jafferabad.', '5', 'Attaullah', 'Yes', 'Male', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Indirect Beneficiary', '03063809807', 'I am a resident of Muhammad Panah Bughatti, Ward No. 26, Deh Barro 02, UC Judhair, Tehsil Jhatpat, District Jafferabad. I am writing to express a serious concern regarding the relief efforts in our area, particularly those undertaken by the organization TKF. Our community has faced severe consequences due to the 2022 flood, leading to the complete destruction of our homes and leaving us without proper shelter and adequate food. During this challenging time, we expected fair and impartial assistance to help us recover. However, it has come to our attention that TKF\'s aid distribution process in our village is marred by discrepancies. It appears that the organization is only considering individuals who contribute a share in 25,000 rupees, documenting their names for assistance. Additionally, a second instalment of 15,000 rupees is reportedly provided only to those who have contributed financially and are deemed favored by the organization. When TKF conducted an assessment in our area, they requested a financial contribution from our community. Unfortunately, due to our inability to comply, our names were allegedly excluded from the survey. Furthermore, while other children in the area received school bags, our children were overlooked, leaving them without this essential item. In light of these concerns, our community is deeply disappointed with the treatment we have received. We kindly request that TKF reconsider and revisit our village during the assessment phase. We believe that a fair and unbiased evaluation of our situation is crucial to ensure that all affected individuals, regardless of their financial capacity, receive the assistance they desperately need. \r\nIsmail Khan 