(1533, '2024-02-21', '1533-1712126658', 'Saba Saeed', 'Close', '2', '49', '5', '19', 'Amlok Bagh', '3', 'Wali Ullah', 'Yes', 'Male', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Indirect Beneficiary', '03453407041', 'I am a PTC teacher at GPS Amlok Bagh. I want to inform you that the rehabilitation work carried out at our school was conducted according to standards and under the supervision of SRSP engineers. The materials used were of good quality. We are satisfied with the rehabilitation work done at the school and would like to express our gratitude to SCI and SRSP for their support.', '3', NULL, 'School rehab', '1', NULL, '5', 'No', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Satisfied', NULL, NULL, NULL, 7, '2024-04-03 06:50:13', NULL, '2024-04-03 06:50:13', NULL, NULL),
(1535, '2024-02-21', '1535-1712127400', 'Saba Saeed', 'Close', '2', '49', '5', '22', 'Teraat', '3', 'Hayat Khan', 'Yes', 'Male', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Indirect Beneficiary', '03488814072', 'As a community member, I commend the construction work at GGPS Teraat. The issue of washroom facilities at the school and access to drinking water in the community has been successfully resolved by SRSP in collaboration with Save the Children. We are deeply grateful for all the interventions.', '3', NULL, 'School rehab', '1', NULL, '6', 'No', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Satisfied', NULL, NULL, NULL, 7, '2024-04-03 07:00:33', NULL, '2024-04-03 07:00:33', NULL, NULL),
(1536, '2024-02-22', '1536-1712128307', 'Saba Saeed', 'Close', '2', '49', '5', '22', 'Teraat', '3', 'Neelam Bibi', 'No', 'Female', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Indirect Beneficiary', NULL, 'There was no boundary wall at the school, which resulted in children being at risk of falling. Additionally, there was a major issue with the water supply, which affected the usability of the washroom facilities. Now, thanks to the assistance of SRSP and SCI, these issues have been successfully resolved. All of this work has been carried out under our supervision, and we are highly satisfied with the results.', '3', NULL, 'School rehab', '1', NULL, '5', 'No', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Satisfied', NULL, NULL, NULL, 7, '2024-04-03 07:24:03', NULL, '2024-04-03 07:24:03', NULL, NULL),
(1537, '2024-03-19', '1537-1712129094', 'Ejaz Shah', 'Close', '2', '49', '5', '19', 'Pardy Shah', '9', 'Hazrat Hussain', 'No', 'Male', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Direct Beneficiary', NULL, 'the contractor has used low-quality material and less cement as a result the stairs have broken from various points, the water tank also leaks, latrine doors cannot be locked from the outside due to the absence of lock assembly, the marble in the washing pad is also detached from the surface and the hand shower in latrine is also not properly fixed.', '3', 'The MEAL manager discussed the feedback with Project Manager SRSP during the debrief session after the monitoring visit.', 'School rehab', '4', NULL, '5', 'Yes', NULL, 'Syed Sajjad', 'Project Manager (SRSP)', NULL, '2024-03-22', NULL, '2024-04-30', 'Satisfied', NULL, NULL, 'The complaint was shared with Project Manager SRSP after monitoring visit by MEAL team along with SRSP staff. It was informed by SRSP staff that contractor was already intimated to complete all the pending work as per quality based on BOQ. SRSP Field engineer will ensure that all rectification work is completed as per BOQ before 20th May 2024. The complaint was closed after satisfactory action taken by the partner.', 7, '2024-04-03 07:35:21', NULL, '2024-05-07 12:22:58', NULL, NULL),
(1538, '2024-03-20', '1538-1712129868', 'Ejaz Shah', 'Close', '2', '49', '5', '24', 'Bahrain', '3', 'Shabir', 'No', 'Male', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Partner Staff', NULL, 'there is a need to raise or protect the boundary wall from the back side of the BHU as it was observed that many drug addicts enter from there and take drugs at night. Secondly, there is a need for proper water drainage from the roof of the newly constructed labor room, therefore, the water falls from everywhere from the roof.', '3', 'The MEAL manager discussed the feedback with Project Manager SRSP during the debrief session after the monitoring visit.', 'BHU rehab work', '4', NULL, '4', 'Yes', NULL, 'Syed Sajjad', 'Project Manager (SRSP)', NULL, '2024-03-22', NULL, '2024-05-06', 'Satisfied', NULL, NULL, 'The SRSP Staff informed that boundary wall of BHU Bahrian has been raised and protected by razor wire, while drainage water from labour room will be resolved during the rectification work before 20th May,2024. The complaint was closed based on satisfactory action taken by the partner.', 7, '2024-04-03 07:40:48', NULL, '2024-05-07 12:08:24', NULL, NULL),
(1539, '2024-03-19', '1539-1712130196', 'Ejaz Shah', 'Close', '2', '49', '5', '24', 'Ossar', '3', 'Tariq Aziz', 'No', 'Male', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Indirect Beneficiary', NULL, 'there is a water leakage from the roof lintel on almost all parts of the roof which needs to be rectified at the earliest.\r\nThe flooring work is of poor quality having rough patches and knocking sounds.\r\nThe stairs in front of the gate are of poor quality having broken edges, without plaster work on the sides, and irregular size of steps. \r\nFurthermore, 100 learning kits and hygiene kits were distributed to the school children. one teaching kit was also provided by SRSP.', '3', 'The MEAL manager discussed the feedback with Project Manager SRSP during the debrief session after the monitoring visit.', 'School rehab', '4', NULL, '5', 'Yes', NULL, 'Syed Sajjad', 'Project Manager (SRSP)', NULL, '2024-03-22', NULL, '2024-05-07', 'Satisfied', NULL, NULL, 'The complaint was shared with Project Manager SRSP and SCI Field Engineer KP. The SRSP Staff informed that the work was delayed due to bad weather. The roof leakage will be resolved by the contractor and other rectification work as pointed out by the complainant will also be completed before 20th May 2024. The site is regularly visited by SRSP field engineer and SCI field Engineer to confirm and review the rehab work. The response was communicated to the complainant, and he was satisfied.', 7, '2024-04-03 07:58:06', NULL, '2024-05-07 12:03:44', NULL, NULL),
(1580, '2024-04-08', '1580-1715056504', 'Fatima Shahani', 'Close', '4', '100', '9', '41', 'Tarai', '6', 'Hakeema', 'Yes', 'Female', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Direct Beneficiary', '03048677518', 'I have received kg grant which I utilized upon the purchasing of fan & solar panels due to non availability of sufficient water for kg cultivation. I am thankful for the assistance.', '3', 'It is a thank you message of a beneficiary who could not utilize the kg grant due to challenges.', 'Validation of livestock beneficiaries', '1', NULL, '3', 'Yes', NULL, 'Aliman Shah', 'FSL Manager', NULL, '2024-05-07', NULL, '2024-04-08', 'Satisfied', NULL, NULL, 'It is positive feedback the beneficiary utilized the grant upon alternate necessities.', 5, '2024-05-07 04:41:37', NULL, '2024-05-07 04:46:21', NULL, NULL),
(1540, '2024-04-05', '1540-1712296861', 'Shahida Khaskheli', 'Close', '4', '100', '9', '90', 'Village Sangher', '6', 'Naheed Hussain', 'No', 'Male', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Direct Beneficiary', NULL, 'I\'m in a dire situation due to losing my home during the 2022 flood. Currently, I lack proper shelter and living conditions. I received your number recently and decided to reach out regarding the shelter assistance assessment. Unfortunately, despite being in significant need and experiencing financial hardship, I wasn\'t evaluated for shelter assistance.', '1', 'Request for assistance was shared with the relevant person to better understands the condition.', 'Shelter', '3', NULL, '5', 'Yes', NULL, 'Raza Khan', 'Shelter & Construction Coordinator - Sindh', NULL, '2024-04-05', NULL, '2024-04-24', 'Partially Satisfied', NULL, NULL, 'The complaint has been brought to the attention of the program team. They have explained that due to budget limitations, it is not feasible to provide carpet coverage and accommodate all community members currently. However, they have noted the complaint for future consideration, and if circumstances allow, they will address it accordingly.', 8, '2024-04-05 06:08:28', NULL, '2024-04-24 05:57:43', NULL, NULL),
(1541, '2024-04-05', '1541-1712297464', 'Shahida Khaskheli', 'Close', '4', '168', '14', '95', 'Darya Khan Shanbani', '5', 'Jameel Ahamd Shanbani', 'Yes', 'Male', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Direct Beneficiary', '03032208195', 'We are immensely grateful to TKF and Save the Children for their presence in our village. Their efforts have been instrumental in providing excellent support for education. The establishment of TLS has created a nurturing and healthy environment for our children to thrive in. I am truly proud of Save the Children for their dedication and impact on our community.', '4', 'Positive feedback has been shared with the project manager.', 'TLS', '1', NULL, '1', 'Yes', NULL, 'Kehkishan Rani', 'Project Manager', NULL, '2024-04-05', NULL, '2024-04-05', 'Satisfied', NULL, NULL, 'Positive feedback has been shared with the program team to encourage the continuity of their excellent work in the future and to express our appreciation for their efforts.', 8, '2024-04-05 06:15:05', NULL, '2024-04-05 06:33:18', NULL, NULL),
(1542, '2024-03-26', '1542-1712297710', 'Shahida Khaskheli', 'Close', '4', '168', '14', '95', 'Darya Khan shanbani', '5', 'Mansoor Ali', 'Yes', 'Male', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Direct Beneficiary', '03004279231', 'In our village, Darya Khan Shanbani, Save the Children and TKF have been doing exceptional work. Our villagers are extremely pleased with the efforts of your organizations. Save the Children, in particular, has brought numerous benefits to our community. School rehabilitation efforts are ongoing, significantly improving educational opportunities for our children. Thanks to Save the Children, there has been a noticeable difference in our children\'s education; they receive free books and bags, while their parents have received 25k cash assistance, providing much-needed relief. Additionally, the staff has been instrumental in raising awareness about climate issues and personal safety and security. We are truly grateful to Save the Children for their invaluable contributions. Thank you so much.', '4', 'Positive feedback has been shared with the project manager.', 'TLS', '1', NULL, '1', 'Yes', NULL, 'Kehkishan Rani', 'Project Manager', NULL, '2024-04-05', NULL, '2024-04-05', 'Satisfied', NULL, NULL, 'Positive feedback has been shared with the program team to encourage the continuity of their excellent work in the future and to express our appreciation for their efforts.', 8, '2024-04-05 06:23:14', NULL, '2024-04-05 06:32:39', NULL, NULL),
(1543, '2024-04-05', '1543-1712298350', 'Shahida Khaskheli', 'Close', '4', '168', '14', '95', 'Darya Khan shanbani', '5', 'Ghulam Jaffer', 'Yes', 'Male', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Direct Beneficiary', '03033216842', 'In our village, TKF and Save the Children are making significant strides in improving our schools. The ongoing repairs at our village school are progressing well, thanks to the dedicated efforts of your team. We are delighted that your organizations chose our village for this educational initiative. Thank you very much for your contributions.', '4', 'Positive feedback has been shared with the relevant person.', 'TLS', '1', NULL, '2', 'Yes', NULL, 'Kehkishan Rani', 'Project Manager', NULL, '2024-04-05', NULL, '2024-04-05', 'Satisfied', NULL, NULL, 'Positive feedback has been shared with the program team to encourage the continuity of their excellent work in the future and to express our appreciation for their efforts.', 8, '2024-04-05 06:30:07', NULL, '2024-04-05 06:32:00', NULL, NULL),
(1544, '2024-04-02', '1540-1712296862', 'Saba Saeed', 'Close', '2', '49', '5', '24', 'Bar Alar', '3', 'Akhtar Ali', 'Yes', 'Male', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Indirect Beneficiary', '03144427942', 'There is a need for development initiatives in our village, Bar Alar. Situated in an area that is currently lacking essential infrastructure such as a water supply scheme and adequate roadways, our community is in dire need of support to improve living conditions.\nI kindly request the consideration of including Bar Alar in any upcoming development projects.', '4', 'the request was initially discussed with MEAL Manager and as per his advise it was shared with Project Manager SRSP for response.', 'Water Supply Scheme', '3', NULL, '6', 'Yes', NULL, 'Syed Sajjad', 'Project Manager (SRSP)', NULL, '2024-04-05', NULL, '2024-04-30', 'Satisfied', NULL, NULL, 'The request for assistance was shared with SRSP. The SRSP Staff met with the respondent and informed him that there is no availability of budget for the construction of infrastructure and water supply schemes. The target of water supply schemes is already achieved from the existing budget. However, in future, subject to availability of funds, the village Bar Alar will be considered for assessments.', 7, '2024-04-05 07:45:03', NULL, '2024-05-07 11:32:09', NULL, NULL),
