(1573, '2024-04-30', '1573-1714729476', 'Shahida Khaskheli', 'Close', '4', '172', '60', '131', 'Village Jisro', '50', 'Ali Murad', 'Yes', 'Male', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Direct Beneficiary', '03490340563', 'I am a resident of village Jadam Daras. Almost two months ago, the TKF team visited our village, listed our names, and we participated in the assessment phase. However, I am seeking information on when we will receive the cash and how much we are entitled to. Kindly guide us as to why such a considerable amount of time has passed without receiving our cash.', '1', 'Complain was shared with the relevant person to better address the condition.', 'FSL', '4', NULL, '3', 'Yes', NULL, 'Aliman Shah', 'FSL Manager', NULL, '2024-04-30', NULL, '2024-04-30', 'Not Satisfied', NULL, NULL, 'The complaint has been shared with the program team, who have informed us that the project beneficiaries data has been sent to Risk and Compliance for review. We anticipate receiving their feedback this week. Cash disbursement will be scheduled accordingly.', 8, '2024-05-03 09:48:23', NULL, '2024-05-08 09:46:41', NULL, NULL),
(1574, '2024-04-29', '1574-1714729722', 'Shahida Khaskheli', 'Close', '4', '168', '54', '127', 'Village Sain Bux Shar', '49', 'Ali Gul', 'Yes', 'Male', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Direct Beneficiary', '03002887627', 'I am resident of Village Sain Bux Shar, initially selected as a general secretary of the village committee, underwent an assessment for KG. However, during the assessment, influential individuals from the village exerted pressure on the assessment team to include their names in the assessment, resulting in the removal of my name from the final list. Additionally, my child was not considered for the Child-Friendly Space (CFS) program too. Despite reaching out to the MRDO team for assistance, i did not received a satisfactory response. This situation is distressing, and it undermines the fairness and integrity of the assessment process. It is imperative that all residents are treated equitably and that assessments are conducted transparently and impartially.', '1', 'The complain was shared with the relevant person to better understand the condition.', 'FSL', '5', NULL, '3', 'Yes', NULL, 'Aliman Shah', 'FSL Manager', NULL, '2024-04-29', NULL, '2024-05-15', 'Partially Satisfied', NULL, NULL, 'Compliant was shared with both CP & FSL sector leads. According to CP Coordinator \"Every child of community is welcomed at CFS and no one can restrict any child for attending CFS. We have confirmed from our CPC that respective child is regularly attending CFS. \r\nFSL Coordinator shared with MEAL that complainant did not qualify for KG assistance and his removal from VC was internal decision of committee which was not based on any political or feudal biasness\"', 8, '2024-05-03 09:54:23', NULL, '2024-06-05 06:10:36', NULL, NULL),
(1575, '2024-05-03', '1575-1714731895', 'Shahida Khaskheli', 'Close', '4', '168', '39', '88', 'Village Bogg', '3', 'Muhammad Ismail', 'Yes', 'Male', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Direct Beneficiary', '03002027393', 'I am a resident of village Bogg Sharif, and this health facility is an essential resource for medical care for us. However, I am very disheartened to report an issue. The female doctor at the facility is not allowing me, along with other patients, to have proper checkups for our children. She simply asks for the patient\'s name and instructs us not to enter the examination room. She then proceeds to write a prescription without conducting a thorough examination. She is neglecting to properly assess the patients, including my 15-day-old child. I am deeply concerned about the lack of proper medical attention. Who will be held responsible for this negligence? I urge you to investigate this matter and take appropriate action to address this ongoing issue.', '1', 'The complain was shared with the relevant person to better understand the complaint.', 'MNC', '5', NULL, '4', 'Yes', NULL, 'Shakeel Patrus', 'Senior Coordinator Health & Nutrition', NULL, '2024-05-03', NULL, '2024-05-13', 'Partially Satisfied', NULL, NULL, 'Complaint was shared with the respective sector lead. According to the H&N Coordinator “I visited the respective facility myself and interviewed respective staff. According to the staff on duty “a large number of individuals visit health facility every day and expect to be treated first, lady doctor never wrote any prescription with examining the child” Behavior of lady doctor was cross verified with the other staff and none of them reported such incident at health facility. Response was communicated back to the caller.', 8, '2024-05-03 10:29:57', NULL, '2024-06-20 07:35:57', NULL, NULL),
