(1600, '2024-04-25', '1600-1715160554', 'Fatima Shahani', 'Close', '4', '100', '9', '41', 'Sindhi Butra', '6', 'Asifa', 'Yes', 'Girl', 'Less than 18 years', 'No', 'Direct Beneficiary', '03101033430', 'This CFS is newly established in our village so I am coming from the first day to spend my time enjoying & learning embroidery. It is my hobby to develop handicrafts for which material is available here & the facilitators provide it to us & teach us embroidery & other life skills so I am feeling very happy for coming to the CFS.', '3', 'It is a positive feedback of a child regarding the CFS.', 'Monitoring Visit', '1', NULL, '1', 'Yes', NULL, 'Nazneen Tabasum', 'CP Coordinator', NULL, '2024-05-08', NULL, '2024-04-25', 'Satisfied', NULL, NULL, 'It is a positive feedback of a child regarding the CFS.', 5, '2024-05-08 09:38:48', NULL, '2024-05-08 09:40:55', NULL, NULL),
(1601, '2024-05-07', '1601-1715167317', 'Fatima Shahani', 'Close', '4', '100', '9', '41', 'Mir Khan Pahi', '6', 'Ghulam Nabi', 'Yes', 'Male', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Direct Beneficiary', '03401865905', 'My house was selected by your organization for shelter construction. The contractor insisted that I undertake earth filling to ensure the continuity of my house construction. I had to expend 10,000 from my own pocket for this purpose, solely to maintain the progress of the shelter work.  Now, I am seeking clarity on who bears the responsibility for the earth filling costs? Given our financial struggles, we are unable to afford such a substantial amount. I kindly request guidance on this mater.', '3', 'Complaint was shared with the technical head to better understand the issue.', 'Shelter Monitoring activity', '5', NULL, '5', 'Yes', NULL, 'Raza Khan', 'Shelter & Construction Coordinator', NULL, '2024-05-08', NULL, '2024-05-15', 'Satisfied', NULL, NULL, 'Complaint was shared with the respective sector lead. According to Coordinator Shelter & Construction “Contractor has shared with us that they never asked any beneficiary for earth-filling inside the shelter and they did it themselves. However, we have returned back all the cost to beneficiary and receipt is submitted to your office” Beneficiary was contacted again and confirmed receiving all the cost they spend on earth-filling.', 8, '2024-05-08 11:31:00', NULL, '2024-06-21 06:04:37', NULL, NULL),
(1602, '2024-05-07', '1602-1715167867', 'Fatima Shahani', 'Close', '4', '100', '9', '41', 'Mir Khan Pahi', '6', 'Abdul raheem', 'Yes', 'Male', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Direct Beneficiary', '03463920984', 'My house was selected by your organization for shelter construction., wherein the contractor has erected an incomplete structure and left it pending for earth filling. Despite this, the contractor is now pressuring us to fill the earth in the shelter and washroom ourselves, now he is emphasizing that we must do so to proceed. Otherwise, he will withhold the shelter construction work. This situation has left me deeply anxious as I am unable to afford the expenses associated with earth filling and I am in a state of financial hardship, I humbly appeal for assistance and guidance in this matter.', '3', 'The complaint was shared with the relevant person to better address the issue.', 'Shelter Monitoring activity', '5', NULL, '5', 'Yes', NULL, 'Raza Khan', 'Shelter & Construction Coordinator', NULL, '2024-05-08', NULL, '2024-05-13', 'Satisfied', NULL, NULL, 'Complaint was shared with the respective sector lead. According to Coordinator Shelter & Construction “Earth-filling inside the shelter & latrine is the responsibility of contractor as per approved BOQs. No beneficiary is required to do so” Caller was contacted again & response was communicated. Later on beneficiaries confirmed that earth-filling was completed by contractor.', 8, '2024-05-08 11:34:25', NULL, '2024-06-21 06:11:30', NULL, NULL),
