(1741, '2024-06-24', '1741-1719392365', 'Ejaz Shah', 'Close', '2', '49', '5', '21', 'GGPS Kas Beshigram', '3', 'Muhammad Raheem', 'Yes', 'Male', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Indirect Beneficiary', '03439236648', 'Received a complaint from Male Parent that his three children enrolled in GGPS Kas Beshigram were given half items in school bags and according to the head teacher the learning kits are not enough for all the enrolled children. The complainant also told that the head teacher has kept the learning kits at home.', '1', 'The complaint was shared with Project Manager SRSP. He informed that he will look into the matter and will respond accordingly.', 'Learning Kits distribution', '4', NULL, '2', 'Yes', NULL, 'Sayyed Sajjad', 'Project Manager SRSP', NULL, '2024-06-24', NULL, '2024-06-28', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A team was sent on 28, June-2024 to check the complaint. It was found that despite of the instructions given by the distribution team, not to split the kits, the Head Teacher had split the kits between enrolled and unenrolled children of pre-nursery. The kits were collected and provided to the entitled enrolled children. The head teacher was advised not to split kits, if she intends to provide kits to the nursery children so they must be enrolled prior kits provision. the matter has resolved.', 4, '2024-06-26 09:03:53', NULL, '2024-08-05 05:34:15', NULL, NULL),
(1742, '2024-06-10', '1742-1719461572', 'Ejaz Shah', 'Close', '2', '49', '5', '20', 'CFW Scheme Ramet', '9', 'Sher Muhammad', 'Yes', 'Male', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Direct Beneficiary', '03139403015', 'I would like to thank Save the Children and SRSP staff for providing irrigation water channel scheme in our area. All the skilled and unskilled labours have received their payments and work was completed satisfactorily.', '1', 'Positive feedback shared with Project Manager SRSP and he felt encouraged. No action was required.', 'CFW Scheme Ramet', '1', NULL, '3', 'Yes', NULL, 'Sayyed Sajjad', 'Project Manager SRSP', NULL, '2024-06-11', NULL, '2024-06-11', 'Satisfied', NULL, NULL, 'Positive feedback received about CFW cash payment to workers. No further action required.', 4, '2024-06-27 04:17:36', NULL, '2024-06-27 04:19:01', NULL, NULL),
(1743, '2024-06-26', '1743-1719485430', 'Fatima Shahani', 'Close', '4', '100', '9', '90', 'Pejaho', '6', 'Muhammad Bachal Mallah', 'No', 'Male', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Direct Beneficiary', NULL, 'In our village 2 water tanks are rehabilitated through your organization but both are empty & non functional since it was handed over due to conflicts among the PHED employees & the community. Therefore the rehabilitated water tanks are not serving the purpose for what they are been rehabilitated for, despite the community is relying on the temporary sources installed through themselves on different points of the village.', '3', 'It is a complaint of a beneficiary regarding the non functionality of the Water Supply Scheme assistance provided under the EU.', 'Field visit of WSS in the community', '5', NULL, '6', 'Yes', NULL, 'Majid Hussain', 'WASH Coordinator', NULL, '2024-06-27', NULL, '2024-07-10', 'Partially Satisfied', NULL, NULL, 'Compliant was shared with the respective Project Manger (IP NRSP). According to him \"Conflict between PHED & Community has been resolved and it was agreed that water will be provided to each water tank in the village\" Response was shared with caller', 5, '2024-06-27 11:09:02', NULL, '2024-09-03 11:45:06', NULL, NULL),
(1744, '2024-06-26', '1744-1719486858', 'Fatima Shahani', 'Close', '4', '100', '9', '90', 'Burira', '6', 'Nisar Ahmed', 'Yes', 'Male', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Direct Beneficiary', '03403628490', 'There are 5 water supply tanks in our village which are rehabilitated through your organization which merely was functional in the first week when handed over to the PHED after that tanks are been not filled & are empty till today. The employees deployed on the WSS source for operating it are giving excuses for not functional it they are asking us to pay them Rupees 200 from each HH to start the source & fill the water tanks but community is unable to pay this amount to purchase water from PHED, therefore we are relying on the temporary sources of water installed in the village on multiple points.', '3', 'It is a complaint of a beneficiary regarding the water tank rehabilitated in his village which is not functional since it was handed over.', 'Field visit of Water tanks of WSS', '5', NULL, '6', 'Yes', NULL, 'Majid Hussain', 'WASH Coordinator', NULL, '2024-06-27', NULL, '2024-07-10', 'Partially Satisfied', NULL, NULL, 'Complaint was shared with the respective Project Manager (NRSP). According to him \"We have contacted senior management of PHED and they have assured us that they will bound local PHED workers to make sure that every water tank is filled & facilitating beneficiaries free of cost\" Response was communicated back to the caller', 5, '2024-06-27 11:25:57', NULL, '2024-09-03 11:49:54', NULL, NULL),
(1745, '2024-06-26', '1745-1719487644', 'Fatima Shahani', 'Close', '4', '100', '9', '90', 'Lahori', '6', 'Ali Hassan', 'Yes', 'Male', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Direct Beneficiary', '3462857673', 'A water tank in our village is rehabilitated through your organization which is non functional since it was handed over to PHED a little amount of water is leaking from the valve through which we barely fetch water. The PHED operator is not supplying water to our water tank & our nearby village Sanghar is only been benefitted from this assistance. We are still deprived from water in spite your organization had tried to make easy access to water for us but all in vain. We have to travel very far in the scorching day light to fetch water which is very challenging for us.', '3', 'It is a complaint of a beneficiary regarding the water tank rehabilitated in his village which is not functional since it was handed over. They are facing very difficult to fetch water from far away.', 'Field visit of Water tanks rehabilitated', '5', NULL, '6', 'Yes', NULL, 'Majid Hussain', 'WASH Coordinator', NULL, '2024-06-27', NULL, '2024-07-04', 'Partially Satisfied', NULL, NULL, 'Complaint was shared with Project Manager (NRSP). According to him \"Water valve has been rehabilitated to control water leakage. Moreover, we have coordinated with district level PHED officials and they have assured that local PHED staff will ensure that all water is supplied to all water tanks\" Response was shared with the caller', 5, '2024-06-27 11:41:56', 103, '2024-09-03 12:05:24', NULL, NULL),
