(1841, '2024-08-09', '1841-1723714154', 'Ejaz Shah', 'Close', '2', '49', '41', '98', 'GPS Bayuon Kalam', '3', 'Hayat ur Rehman', 'Yes', 'Male', '19-50 years', 'No', 'Direct Beneficiary', '03139077088', 'The pace of rehab work is very slow; the contractor is not properly doing the work. Moreover, there are 270 children enrolled in the school but learning kits were provided to only a few children.', '1', 'Complaint Shared with Project Manager SRSP.', 'School Rehab work', '4', NULL, '5', 'Yes', NULL, 'Sayyed Sajjad Shah', 'Project Manager SRSP', NULL, '2024-08-09', NULL, '2024-08-09', 'Satisfied', NULL, NULL, 'The Project Manager SRSP shared that We had a meeting with contractors on 7, Aug-2024 stressing to expedite the work on all sites to meet the deadline. It was assured by the contractors to increase labour numbers and we are having follow ups on this. We will be able to complete the rehab work of GPS Bayoun Kalam till 15, Aug-2024.\r\n\r\nLearning and Education kits were provided to current phase\'s 8 schools before summer vocations. There are four schools left namely; GPS Garilagan, GPS Bayoun Kalam, GPS Ashoran, and GGPS Kwaro Tangy. They have been planned to be provided Education and Learning kits between 12 to 16, Aug-2024. Please be noted all children enrolled after kits distribution in the earlier 8 schools, will also receive learning kits as part of the plan. The complaint was closed based on the action taken by partner.', 4, '2024-08-15 09:37:52', NULL, '2024-08-15 09:43:24', NULL, NULL),
